                  <additions><list>
                    <item xml:id="e1"><desc><locus target="#ir" facs="001"/>Contains the date <date calendar="ethiopian">Ḥamle 6, 19[1]5 E.C.</date>. The space for the tens digit has been prepared for a number, but no number has been added (<foreign xml:lang="gez">፲፱፻[ ]፭ ዓመት፡ ሐምሌ፡ ፮ቀን፡</foreign>)</desc></item>
                    <item xml:id="a1"><desc type="OwnershipNote"><locus target="#10r" facs="012">f. 10r and passim</locus> mention the owner Wäldä Giyorgis (<foreign xml:lang="gez">ወልደ፡ ጊዮርጊስ፡</foreign>)</desc></item>
                    <item xml:id="a2"><desc><locus target="#138r #144r" facs="140 146"/> mentions <persName ref="PRS6876Matewos"/></desc></item>
                    <item xml:id="a3"><desc><locus target="#144r #144v #145v" facs="146 147 148"/> mentions <persName ref="PRS10671Zawditu"/></desc></item>
                    <item xml:id="a4"><desc>Every so often in the book, a section of text is written in small writing (e.g., <locus target="#43v #44r #67 #68r" facs="046 070"/>).
                    These contain collections of chants. </desc></item>
                    <item xml:id="e2"><desc>In most places where the departed are to be mentioned by name, a blank space is left in the manuscript (e.g., <locus target="#38v" facs="041"/>)</desc></item>
                    <item xml:id="e3"><desc>Numbered quires 2–18.</desc></item>
                    <item xml:id="e4"><desc>
                      Scribal intervention:
                      words of text are written interlinearly,  <locus target="#7r #8v #14v #35v #45r" facs="009 011 017 038 047"/>, etc.);
                      text has been removed (<locus target="#6v #23r #44v #45r #51v"  facs="009 025 047 047 054"/>, etc.)</desc>
                    </item>
                  </list></additions>

